    <name>
      <text>8.2.16 (Sum of AP given terms)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>What is the sum of the first {@nval@} terms of the arithmetic progression \({@S4@}+\ldots\)?&nbsp;</p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We have \(S_n=\dfrac{n(\text{first term} + \text{last term})}{2}\). We know \(n={@nval@}\) and the first term is \(a={@aval@}\), so all we need to do is work out the last term. The common difference is \(d={@dval@}\), so the last term will be \[u_{@nval@}=a+({@nval@}-1)d={@last_term@}.\]</p><p>Thus \[&nbsp;S_{@nval@}&nbsp;= \frac{{@nval@}({@aval@} + {@last_term@})}{2}={@sum_n@}.\]</p><p>Alternatively, you may choose to remember that the sum \(S_{n}\) of an arithmetic progression of \(n\) terms, first term \(a\) and common difference \(d\), is \(S_n=\frac{n}{2}(2a+(n-1)d)\). Here \(a={@aval@}\) and \(d={@dval@}\) so \(S_{@nval@}={@sum_n@}\).</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
